Package aquarium.creatures

Contains the collection of classes implementing Creature which are then added to the Aquarium.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Creature
    A Creature inhabits an Aquarium and primarily has a name, location, and appearance.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChangingSwimmer
    A ChangingSwimmer is a PaintedCreature which: Moves at a given whole integer slope speed, in a straight line; Can change X and Y speeds after being created; Bounces off of the walls, the floor, and the surface of the water, in order to stay underwater.
    LineSwimmer
    A LineSwimmer is a PaintedCreature which: Moves at a given whole integer slope speed, in a straight line; Bounces off of the walls, the floor, and the surface of the water, in order to stay underwater.
    PaintedCreature
    A Creature which has an appearance it paints on its own.

Package aquarium.creatures Description

Contains the collection of classes implementing Creature which are then added to the Aquarium.
